<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06156j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06156j">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06156j"> 156(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prayer of faithful / Paternoster</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">PART IV. CHRISTIAN PRAYER. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> THE LORD&apos;S PRAYER. In the primitive Church this prayer was used only in the Communion Service, and was called &ldquo;<mark>the prayer of the faithful</mark>.&rdquo; <p>The LORD&apos;S PRAYER may be divided into three parts. First, Introduction or address; Secondly, seven Petitions; Thirdly, the Doxology. The first three petitions relate to the glory of God: the last four to our common wants.</p> <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 43-4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
